BurglaryToPointOfInterestDistance

September 9, 2015

We take a subset of burglary data so that contains only 2008-2014 records to relieve computational burden. The regular grid is made by setting up a 120 $$ 160 grid then constraint it by keeping those inside the city boundary, in which 7724 grids are included.

Now we explore burglary in proximity to some spatial points of interest. They are all calculated in the same fasion that for each incident/grid we calculate the Euclidean distance between that point to the closest landmarks.
